Introduction

SECRET NUMBER is a two-member girl group formed by Vine Entertainment. Initially scheduled to debut on March 26, 2020, their debut was delayed due to the global outbreak of COVID-19. The group officially debuted on May 19, 2020, with the single "Who Dis?".

On September 29, 2021, Vine Entertainment announced that member Denise would not participate in the group's upcoming comeback due to ongoing contract negotiations. This was followed by the announcement of the single "Fire Saturday" on October 27, 2021, along with the addition of new members Minji and Zuu.

Denise confirmed her departure from both the group and Vine Entertainment on Instagram on February 5, 2022. Three years later, on April 2, 2025, Vine Entertainment announced on their social media that Léa had chosen to leave the group and company. On April 4, Jinny, Dita, and Minji released a collective statement announcing their departures from the group and company as well.
